      "writtenOn": "2019-06-13T15:27:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Not sure if this is worth mentioning: the following edge case is not correctly handled by this implementation:\n1. GCS file A is added with contents \"foo\" and ingested\n2. GCS file A is modified to have contents \"bar\" and ingested; new data overwrites the data from step 1.\n3. GCS file A is modified to have contents \"foo\" again. Ingester ignores this update, and Gold continues to use the data from step 2.",
      "revId": "431179fefca670952d70539b63b6dbb1ec652e08",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
